1
00:04:03,240 --> 00:04:06,280
Rivetot,
what in the world are you doing?

2
00:04:06,440 --> 00:04:09,120
- I wasn't going to kill him.
- Kill who? What?

3
00:04:09,320 --> 00:04:11,000
- The dog!
- Which dog?

4
00:04:11,160 --> 00:04:13,840
A red dog.
It's the first one I've ever seen.

5
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:16,440
He crossed the street
just in front of us.

6
00:04:16,600 --> 00:04:19,720
I almost got him,
did you get hurt?

7
00:04:19,880 --> 00:04:23,120
So where is that dog?
We could adopt him.

8
00:04:23,240 --> 00:04:24,040
No. But..

9
00:04:25,240 --> 00:04:26,880
Hell, I wasn't dreaming!

10
00:04:27,080 --> 00:04:29,120
A huge dog, scarlet red.

11
00:04:29,320 --> 00:04:31,160
He looked as if he was blood-soaked.

12
00:04:31,320 --> 00:04:32,760
- I don't know.
- I'm not crazy.

13
00:04:32,960 --> 00:04:35,200
You must have
fallen asleep for a moment,

14
00:04:36,040 --> 00:04:38,760
or you had a hallucination.

15
00:04:48,480 --> 00:04:51,440
Boy! Right in front of the wheel.
What happened?

16
00:04:51,600 --> 00:04:53,480
A giant dog,
with feverish,

17
00:04:53,720 --> 00:04:55,320
very sparkling eyes.
- You, too?

18
00:04:55,480 --> 00:04:57,320
There, Michel! I wasn't dreaming.

19
00:04:57,560 --> 00:04:59,560
Let's see!
This region is famous for it.

20
00:04:59,720 --> 00:05:02,800
A big red dog keeps crossing
the streets around here,

21
00:05:02,960 --> 00:05:05,600
to test the driver's reactions.

22
00:05:08,120 --> 00:05:10,480
Hey! Look out!

23
00:05:10,640 --> 00:05:13,280
Stop! Stop!

24
00:05:17,040 --> 00:05:19,880
- I'm lost.
- The beast must have left,

25
00:05:20,040 --> 00:05:22,040
or it's scared to get a beating.

26
00:05:22,200 --> 00:05:24,360
- Don't joke about it.
- What do we do?

27
00:05:24,520 --> 00:05:26,320
We wait for nightfall,

28
00:05:26,480 --> 00:05:29,880
to see the dog dancing
the rumba in our headlights?

29
00:05:30,040 --> 00:05:31,880
- Or we can leave right away?
- Hey! Ho!

30
00:05:32,320 --> 00:05:34,160
Wait one minute!

31
00:05:36,040 --> 00:05:38,520
I know you!
You're Michel Mortez.

32
00:05:38,720 --> 00:05:41,760
Unbelievable. Come,
let's take a picture. Madeleine!

33
00:05:42,400 --> 00:05:43,920
Attention.

34
00:05:44,120 --> 00:05:46,800
Sir, don't move,
you'll be out of focus. Good.

35
00:05:48,360 --> 00:05:49,800
Smile.

36
00:05:52,200 --> 00:05:53,360
Thanks.

37
00:06:22,760 --> 00:06:26,480
Rivetot! Light my way, please.
I can't see anything.

38
00:06:27,200 --> 00:06:28,600
Ah! Thanks.

39
00:06:29,920 --> 00:06:34,320
Hello? Hello, love, it's me.
Yes, it's me, darling.

40
00:06:34,480 --> 00:06:39,360
Ah! Yes. Not at all!
Do what you have to.

41
00:06:39,920 --> 00:06:42,320
April, in Rio, certainly.

42
00:06:42,480 --> 00:06:45,520
How great! How lucky!

43
00:06:46,040 --> 00:06:47,920
What?
No, don't change anything for me.

44
00:06:48,080 --> 00:06:51,760
If you have a meeting, I don't
want you to be late because of me.

45
00:06:51,920 --> 00:06:53,360
Please.

46
00:06:54,400 --> 00:06:55,880
Of course!

47
00:06:57,000 --> 00:06:58,960
I, kiss you?

48
00:06:59,360 --> 00:07:02,720
Yes, I kiss you everywhere.

49
00:07:10,360 --> 00:07:12,800
- How are you?
- It isn't easy, you know?

50
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:16,320
- At least she loves you.
- So she says.

51
00:07:25,920 --> 00:07:29,880
We have a reservation
under Mortez et Rivetot.

52
00:07:30,440 --> 00:07:33,600
Oh! Yes!
You're the gentlemen from the radio.

53
00:07:33,760 --> 00:07:38,680
M. Mortez! Here, there are
two rooms reserved for you.

54
00:07:38,920 --> 00:07:40,760
We expected you earlier.

55
00:07:40,920 --> 00:07:43,800
We were held up by
a red dog with yellow eyes.

56
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:45,520
Oh, no!
Rabies?

57
00:07:45,720 --> 00:07:48,880
Don't worry, dear lady,
the beast didn't dare.

58
00:07:49,040 --> 00:07:51,600
Don't worry,
I'll live through it.

59
00:07:51,760 --> 00:07:56,760
Really? You scared me.
Strange things happen.

60
00:07:59,480 --> 00:08:02,200
Say, do you have
one room with two beds?

61
00:08:02,360 --> 00:08:05,760
- Yes, why?
- We'll take that one.

62
00:08:05,920 --> 00:08:09,520
- We'd reserved two rooms.
- Yes,

63
00:08:09,720 --> 00:08:11,920
but...

64
00:08:12,080 --> 00:08:14,360
No. We changed our mind.
We'll only take one.

65
00:08:14,520 --> 00:08:17,640
I have the two rooms,
and others, if you want.

66
00:08:17,800 --> 00:08:18,760
It's very quiet.

67
00:08:18,960 --> 00:08:21,400
My chauffeur has type B Diabetes.

68
00:08:21,640 --> 00:08:25,240
He needs constant care.

69
00:08:25,440 --> 00:08:29,200
If I'm not there with him,
he may be dead tomorrow morning.

70
00:08:29,360 --> 00:08:33,240
This would have repercussions
on the reputation of your hotel.

71
00:08:33,440 --> 00:08:35,920
That's why we need
a room with two beds.

72
00:08:36,040 --> 00:08:38,040
I wasn't aware of this.
Forgive me.

73
00:08:38,240 --> 00:08:41,200
- Should I take the bags?
- No, thank you, we'll be ok.

74
00:08:42,480 --> 00:08:45,800
- I look like an idiot.
- At all!

75
00:08:58,040 --> 00:08:59,680
Michel! What's wrong?

76
00:09:00,600 --> 00:09:02,480
Michel! Are you ok?
Can you hear me?

77
00:09:03,360 --> 00:09:05,480
- Michel!
- What's wrong with him?

78
00:09:05,720 --> 00:09:09,240
Nothing, bring the stuff
to our room, Michel, are you ok?

79
00:09:10,520 --> 00:09:11,560
I'm fine.

80
00:09:11,760 --> 00:09:13,200
There, get up, hep!

81
00:09:14,080 --> 00:09:15,520
There we have it.

82
00:09:15,720 --> 00:09:18,200
I'm diabetic
and you faint on us!

83
00:09:18,360 --> 00:09:20,920
Come on, walk straight,
there's the landlady.

84
00:09:30,200 --> 00:09:32,240
You didn't see anything:
nothing happened.

85
00:09:33,120 --> 00:09:35,280
Are you ok? Alright.

86
00:09:36,080 --> 00:09:40,200
- So you like the room, sirs?
- Good, very good.

87
00:09:41,320 --> 00:09:43,240
Very nice.

88
00:09:47,320 --> 00:09:48,240
Please!

89
00:09:48,880 --> 00:09:51,440
- Is there a restaurant?
- Excuse me?

90
00:09:51,600 --> 00:09:52,720
Can we have dinner?

91
00:09:52,920 --> 00:09:56,360
I'm afraid you can't at this hour.

92
00:09:56,560 --> 00:09:58,160
I must insist, madame.

93
00:09:58,320 --> 00:10:02,880
It was a long and hard trip,
now we'd like to eat a bite.

94
00:10:03,120 --> 00:10:06,480
I'll check if my husband can
heat anything up for you.

95
00:10:06,720 --> 00:10:09,720
We'll take a quick shower
and be back down.

96
00:10:14,480 --> 00:10:16,720
Are you finished?
Can I bring the desert?

97
00:10:17,600 --> 00:10:19,760
- Yes, thanks.
- It was delicious.

98
00:10:20,160 --> 00:10:23,440
- There's only one slice of cake.
- Thank you, miss.

99
00:10:23,560 --> 00:10:24,480
Is it home-made?

100
00:10:24,640 --> 00:10:27,360
Yes, not in this home,
but it's very good.

101
00:10:27,520 --> 00:10:28,760
Great, should we share?

102
00:10:28,920 --> 00:10:32,160
- Take the fruit, I love the dough.
- Delphine!

103
00:10:39,840 --> 00:10:42,200
Shit, I don't understand.
5 000 Francs are missing.

104
00:10:43,320 --> 00:10:46,160
- You hear?
- You miscalculated.

105
00:10:47,760 --> 00:10:49,200
It's all my fault.

106
00:10:49,440 --> 00:10:53,160
- It always is.
- Easy, you!

107
00:10:53,840 --> 00:10:55,080
Did you steal it?

108
00:10:56,080 --> 00:10:58,440
- It isn't your money.
- No, it isn't,

109
00:10:59,040 --> 00:11:00,880
but I'm responsible for it.

110
00:11:01,200 --> 00:11:03,080
So, it's you?

111
00:11:04,440 --> 00:11:06,760
Is everything satisfying?
Did you like the meal?

112
00:11:06,960 --> 00:11:09,160
It was perfect.

113
00:11:14,000 --> 00:11:15,160
If I'd asked you for 5 000 F,

114
00:11:15,360 --> 00:11:17,680
- would you have lent them to me?
- Of course, not.

115
00:11:17,840 --> 00:11:18,640
See?

116
00:11:19,880 --> 00:11:22,760
I knew it was you.
I'm disgusted.

117
00:11:22,880 --> 00:11:25,800
I calculated it.
33 000 are missing.

118
00:11:26,000 --> 00:11:27,200
How can we account for that?

119
00:11:27,360 --> 00:11:29,560
- Stop moaning, I'll give it back.
- Really?

120
00:11:29,720 --> 00:11:30,520
When?

121
00:11:31,000 --> 00:11:32,680
Whenever you want, buddy.

122
00:11:32,880 --> 00:11:36,320
Tonight, if you want.
I'll give them to you, this evening.

123
00:11:37,560 --> 00:11:38,320
Say,

124
00:11:38,520 --> 00:11:41,920
is the casino of your borough
open this season?

125
00:11:42,080 --> 00:11:43,040
Hem,..no.

126
00:11:43,280 --> 00:11:46,080
- Closed.
- Shame.

127
00:11:46,280 --> 00:11:48,320
- Good evening, Sirs.
- Goodnight.

128
00:11:49,000 --> 00:11:52,040
5 000 F more or less,
I don't see the problem.

129
00:11:52,200 --> 00:11:54,480
I'm fed up with
bailing you out.

130
00:11:54,720 --> 00:11:57,880
I'm sorry for you, Rivetot.
You can be so petty!

131
00:11:58,040 --> 00:12:00,600
"Petty"?
Look who's talking!

132
00:12:00,760 --> 00:12:03,960
Because of your debts,
we have to stay in dubious hotels,

133
00:12:04,160 --> 00:12:06,040
and share a room,
to save money!

134
00:12:06,200 --> 00:12:09,080
- I've no more privacy!
- As if you needed any!

135
00:12:09,520 --> 00:12:13,480
It may be true, Michel.
Take it easy.

136
00:12:14,720 --> 00:12:17,240
I'm tired.
I'm going to bed.

137
00:12:18,120 --> 00:12:19,400
Good night.

138
00:12:23,880 --> 00:12:28,480
It's been twenty years,
aren't' you tired of it?

139
00:12:28,640 --> 00:12:31,040
Since the Cat's Tongue's beginning,

140
00:12:31,200 --> 00:12:34,320
I added it up,
I asked 94 203 questions

141
00:12:34,480 --> 00:12:38,240
and met 18 603 candidates.

142
00:12:38,440 --> 00:12:40,800
I'm not like those
actors in theatres,

143
00:12:40,960 --> 00:12:43,680
always saying the same lines,
on the same cues,

144
00:12:43,880 --> 00:12:46,240
to the same partners
every evening, no.

145
00:12:46,400 --> 00:12:49,040
For me it's different every time.

146
00:12:49,200 --> 00:12:51,800
So, you see,
I'm not tired of it.

147
00:12:51,960 --> 00:12:56,200
Michel! You'll be late for the
selection of the candidates.

148
00:12:56,360 --> 00:12:59,360
- I'm not done with my interview.
- They're waiting.

149
00:12:59,520 --> 00:13:01,760
Go, M. Mortez, don't worry.

150
00:13:01,880 --> 00:13:05,400
- You've only asked two questions.
- That's ok.

151
00:13:05,560 --> 00:13:07,280
When were you here last time?

152
00:13:07,480 --> 00:13:10,800
I don't know.
Two years ago, in march. Why?

153
00:13:10,960 --> 00:13:15,200
I'll look in the archives,
and copy the article.

154
00:13:15,360 --> 00:13:18,040
- Goodbye, Sirs.
- Goodbye.

155
00:13:23,480 --> 00:13:25,120
That little asshole!

156
00:13:29,680 --> 00:13:30,480
Who hits it?

157
00:13:31,240 --> 00:13:34,320
Hold on a minute!
Do you know how much that's worth?

158
00:13:34,480 --> 00:13:36,560
Come closer.
We can't hear you.

159
00:13:36,760 --> 00:13:41,760
Let's repeat the applause.
When I raise my arm, you applaud.

160
00:13:41,920 --> 00:13:44,280
When I lower it,
you're quiet. OK?

161
00:13:44,440 --> 00:13:46,040
Let's try it. Attention!

162
00:13:48,040 --> 00:13:50,840
Well?
Is that what you call an applause?

163
00:13:51,000 --> 00:13:52,960
You ought to be ten times louder.

164
00:13:53,400 --> 00:13:54,480
Go on!

165
00:13:57,040 --> 00:14:00,520
There! Formidable!
You're formidable!

166
00:14:02,440 --> 00:14:05,200
You're on in 1 minute 30 seconds.

167
00:14:05,360 --> 00:14:07,920
- OK. Is it sunny in Paris?
- Not really, and you?

168
00:14:08,040 --> 00:14:09,080
Rather shitty.

169
00:14:09,240 --> 00:14:10,520
You gotta hang in there.

170
00:14:10,680 --> 00:14:12,560
In two months,
you're in the studio.

171
00:14:12,720 --> 00:14:13,760
What?

172
00:14:13,920 --> 00:14:17,040
Haven't you heard?
Mortez'show is off.

173
00:14:17,640 --> 00:14:18,920
You're joking?

174
00:14:19,040 --> 00:14:22,360
- We've known it for a week.
- I don't believe it.

175
00:14:22,600 --> 00:14:25,840
There must be a mistake
Did they just change the slot?

176
00:14:26,040 --> 00:14:29,240
Philippe, listen!
Check if they changed the slot.

177
00:14:29,400 --> 00:14:32,280
And guess what replaced it?
Hello?

178
00:14:32,480 --> 00:14:34,640
Airing in 30 seconds.
Go! On you.

179
00:14:34,800 --> 00:14:36,760
Thank you, Jerome,
for this clubbing hit.

180
00:14:36,920 --> 00:14:40,080
It's time for
our daily hour with Michel Mortez

181
00:14:40,240 --> 00:14:41,240
who's in Marez

182
00:14:41,480 --> 00:14:44,000
for his game,
the Cat's Tongue.

183
00:14:44,200 --> 00:14:46,680
Maréziens, how are you?

184
00:14:48,280 --> 00:14:49,800
Today we are in

185
00:14:50,040 --> 00:14:52,840
Marez,
in the Friac county,

186
00:14:53,000 --> 00:14:56,440
where we'll be next week, as well.

187
00:14:57,960 --> 00:14:59,280
And?

188
00:15:00,760 --> 00:15:05,040
Marez prises itself
home of a XII century castle,

189
00:15:05,240 --> 00:15:08,800
unfortunately damaged
in the bombings of 1944.

190
00:15:08,960 --> 00:15:11,640
Marez,
city of flowers and smiles,

191
00:15:11,760 --> 00:15:14,640
whose packaging
and household items industry

192
00:15:14,760 --> 00:15:16,840
are famous throughout France.

193
00:15:22,320 --> 00:15:24,880
Don't ever do this again!

194
00:15:25,920 --> 00:15:29,560
M. Vaillant, you're too young
to have seen the 1944 ruins.

195
00:15:29,720 --> 00:15:31,960
Since when do you live in Marez?

196
00:15:32,120 --> 00:15:34,120
I came here six years ago.

197
00:15:34,280 --> 00:15:37,080
You're a science teacher
at the Marez High school?

198
00:15:37,240 --> 00:15:39,320
Indeed.
Physics and Chemistry.

199
00:15:39,520 --> 00:15:42,760
Physics and chemistry
aren't very popular.

200
00:15:42,960 --> 00:15:44,600
I envie the drawing teachers.

201
00:15:45,280 --> 00:15:47,880
"It's an australian state,
a port in Canada,

202
00:15:48,040 --> 00:15:51,560
"a lake in equatorial Africa..."
- It's his voice.

203
00:15:52,960 --> 00:15:55,640
Hello, I'm the repairman...

204
00:15:56,040 --> 00:15:57,800
What timing!

205
00:15:59,640 --> 00:16:02,360
Attention! Only five seconds!

206
00:16:04,240 --> 00:16:07,680
Ah, I... I know it.

207
00:16:09,360 --> 00:16:10,360
I know it.

208
00:16:10,920 --> 00:16:11,960
The answer?

209
00:16:12,160 --> 00:16:14,040
Are you giving your Cat's Tongue?

210
00:16:14,640 --> 00:16:15,840
Well, yes.

211
00:16:16,040 --> 00:16:19,840
I'm sorry, many listeners
must have known the answer.

212
00:16:20,000 --> 00:16:22,240
It was the Victoria falls.

213
00:16:23,200 --> 00:16:24,160
I knew it.

214
00:16:24,360 --> 00:16:26,480
- I was afraid I'd be wrong.
- Sorry.

215
00:16:26,680 --> 00:16:29,600
This was an easy question.

216
00:16:31,080 --> 00:16:34,040
"Born in 1778,
died in Paris in 1850,

217
00:16:34,240 --> 00:16:36,360
"he worked on gas expansion.

218
00:16:36,520 --> 00:16:38,440
"and announced some basic laws,

219
00:16:38,640 --> 00:16:41,360
"like, for instance,
thermic coefficiency.

220
00:16:41,560 --> 00:16:45,480
"The name of this french physicist
is worth ten points.

221
00:16:45,680 --> 00:16:47,160
"his christian name Louis-Joseph."

222
00:16:47,360 --> 00:16:49,720
Everybody knows
Louis-Joseph Gay-Lussac!

223
00:16:49,920 --> 00:16:52,880
Sir, it wasn't your turn
to answer!

224
00:16:53,080 --> 00:16:57,200
I'm sorry, madame,
but what difference does it make,

225
00:16:57,400 --> 00:16:59,720
you already
were comfortably ahead.

226
00:16:59,920 --> 00:17:03,720
- You're putting it all at stake?
- No, I prefer to stop here.

227
00:17:03,920 --> 00:17:07,080
As you wish,
the jackpot increases of 1 000 F

228
00:17:07,240 --> 00:17:09,840
and tomorrow will be at 27 000 F.

229
00:17:10,000 --> 00:17:13,480
See you tomorrow,
at the Cat's Tongue.

230
00:17:13,640 --> 00:17:18,080
Maréziennes et Maréziens,
be well!

231
00:17:28,360 --> 00:17:31,880
Philippe?
Were you bullshitting me?

232
00:17:32,040 --> 00:17:34,400
Which language should we speak?

233
00:17:34,560 --> 00:17:37,920
The show is cancelled.
Mortez is out.

234
00:17:38,080 --> 00:17:39,720
Why weren't we informed?

235
00:17:39,920 --> 00:17:44,360
We should be, soon.
It went out with today's mail.

236
00:17:44,520 --> 00:17:48,440
Good luck for telling
the old man . See you!

237
00:17:56,560 --> 00:17:58,320
You're horrible.

238
00:18:04,640 --> 00:18:07,800
- Michel, can I speak to you?
- Just one moment.

239
00:18:07,960 --> 00:18:08,960
It's important.

240
00:18:18,760 --> 00:18:19,960
Michel!

241
00:18:20,920 --> 00:18:22,840
Michel! Get up, Michel!

242
00:18:23,600 --> 00:18:25,040
It's nothing. Michel!

243
00:18:26,960 --> 00:18:29,520
I don't see the point
of exhausting you like this,

244
00:18:29,680 --> 00:18:31,600
if we have to
keep you going like this.

245
00:18:31,800 --> 00:18:34,840
You're giving me lessons?
You want any? You sound like papa.

246
00:18:35,680 --> 00:18:39,640
You know, Michel, maybe you have
to stop before it's too late.

247
00:18:40,360 --> 00:18:44,360
One has to stop
when one's at the peak.

248
00:18:44,560 --> 00:18:45,800
Over my dead body.

249
00:18:45,960 --> 00:18:50,360
With a syringe up my arse
I'd get up on stage.

250
00:18:50,520 --> 00:18:53,520
And that's
where you can put your lessons.

251
00:19:17,000 --> 00:19:20,120
- Can I have an autograph?
- Certainly.

252
00:19:21,080 --> 00:19:23,560
- What's your name?
- Michel, like you.

253
00:19:23,720 --> 00:19:26,800
"For Michel", signed "Michel".

254
00:19:26,960 --> 00:19:29,440
- Thank you, M. Mortez.
- Oh, please.

255
00:19:31,160 --> 00:19:33,240
What did you want to tell me,
earlier?

256
00:19:33,400 --> 00:19:37,240
Huh?
Nothing important.

257
00:19:39,400 --> 00:19:43,480
- Are you leaving today?
- Yes, why?

258
00:19:44,120 --> 00:19:47,440
- Do you have a better idea?
- No, I was just asking.

259
00:19:47,600 --> 00:19:48,960
It's always the same.

260
00:19:49,120 --> 00:19:52,400
A different city every day.
We don't have time to get attached.

261
00:19:52,560 --> 00:19:57,160
- Do you love your job?
- Not bad, we see lots of places.

262
00:19:57,320 --> 00:19:59,560
- We did Switzerland and Belgium.
- Really?

263
00:19:59,720 --> 00:20:03,200
Hotels, restaurants,
the road, all the time,

264
00:20:03,360 --> 00:20:05,320
male friends, tout ça...

265
00:20:06,880 --> 00:20:11,120
I owe the great success
of this show to you,

266
00:20:11,280 --> 00:20:15,840
and the audience, which ...
since 15 years, no, 20, 25 years,

267
00:20:16,000 --> 00:20:18,120
follows, listens and encourages me.

268
00:20:18,280 --> 00:20:22,960
I drink to your fidelity,
ladies and gentlemen. Cheers!

269
00:20:23,760 --> 00:20:24,760
Delicious!

270
00:20:24,920 --> 00:20:27,840
This isn't just a decor,
Let's eat.

271
00:20:28,240 --> 00:20:32,720
- Go. Hello, girls!
- Are you coming back?

272
00:20:32,880 --> 00:20:35,440
Oh, if we ever get back here,

273
00:20:35,600 --> 00:20:38,800
you'll be married with children,
a family and all that,

274
00:20:38,960 --> 00:20:41,440
- You're lucky.
- Do you have children?

275
00:20:41,600 --> 00:20:43,800
No, I'd love to,
but Mortez doesn't want any.

276
00:20:43,960 --> 00:20:47,800
It wouldn't be good for the kid:
a different school every day..

277
00:20:49,200 --> 00:20:52,760
There, little Mareziennes, behave!

278
00:20:52,920 --> 00:20:54,400
And when the direction announced

279
00:20:54,560 --> 00:20:56,720
that they wanted
the show for another 10 years,

280
00:20:56,880 --> 00:20:59,720
I couldn't believe it.
And yet, it was true.

281
00:20:59,880 --> 00:21:00,760
It's marvel...

282
00:21:00,920 --> 00:21:04,720
Oh! There it's for me.
My driver awaits me.

283
00:21:05,160 --> 00:21:08,760
I'm chatting away,
but we have a long road ahead.

284
00:21:09,160 --> 00:21:12,280
Thanks for everything,
thank you all.

285
00:21:12,440 --> 00:21:16,240
Maréziennes, Maréziens,
be well.

286
00:21:19,680 --> 00:21:22,520
Say, M. Mortez,
I'm sorry for earlier.

287
00:21:22,680 --> 00:21:25,200
It's ok.
You'll do better next time.

288
00:21:25,360 --> 00:21:28,640
Especially because I knew
the answer, the Victoria falls.

289
00:21:28,800 --> 00:21:32,480
Everybody knew it.
You had a blank. Goodbye

290
00:21:32,960 --> 00:21:36,120
Yes, speaking of blanks,
we're going to Mézoches-le-Château.

291
00:21:36,280 --> 00:21:38,040
Indeed.

292
00:21:43,120 --> 00:21:43,880
Look.

293
00:21:44,080 --> 00:21:47,240
- That's the fourth one.
- The fourth what?

294
00:21:47,440 --> 00:21:48,760
That man on the bridge.

295
00:21:49,200 --> 00:21:51,960
I wonder what they're doing there.
you've got to be bored to death.

296
00:21:52,080 --> 00:21:53,440
He doesn't bother anyone.

297
00:21:53,640 --> 00:21:57,280
He bothers me. One day,
one of them will go crazy.

298
00:21:57,480 --> 00:21:59,320
he'll throw his bike on a car.

299
00:22:00,080 --> 00:22:01,800
You'll see, Michel.

300
00:22:14,000 --> 00:22:18,600
I'm not a fan of it,
besides it makes you thirsty.

301
00:22:18,760 --> 00:22:21,160
You could have gotten
a thermos with champagne.

302
00:22:23,520 --> 00:22:26,360
Enough,
I'm becoming nauseous.

303
00:22:29,520 --> 00:22:31,480
You, you threw up?

304
00:22:32,600 --> 00:22:34,080
I don't understand!

305
00:22:34,600 --> 00:22:37,480
When you don't digest well,
you shouldn't be eating.

306
00:22:37,640 --> 00:22:39,160
It's a waste.

307
00:23:23,760 --> 00:23:27,000
In my parent's house,
the gas counter was in the garage.

308
00:23:27,160 --> 00:23:29,640
When I was little,
I spent hours in front of the dial,

309
00:23:29,800 --> 00:23:31,520
watching the numbers turn.

310
00:23:32,680 --> 00:23:34,560
The ones on the right turn faster.

311
00:23:34,720 --> 00:23:37,480
At ten,
the two last numbers both change.

312
00:23:37,640 --> 00:23:39,920
To see three change,
you had to wait a lot.

313
00:23:40,080 --> 00:23:44,680
Four numbers, very rare.
It almost never happened.

314
00:23:44,840 --> 00:23:48,320
I came at lunch time,
when the numbers turned quickly.

315
00:23:48,480 --> 00:23:50,040
I said to myself:

316
00:23:50,200 --> 00:23:53,240
"I'll wait for three numbers
to change, and I'll leave."

317
00:23:53,440 --> 00:23:56,400
I spent so much time
in front of that counter!

318
00:23:56,520 --> 00:23:57,800
Now that everything's electric,

319
00:23:57,960 --> 00:24:00,320
your childhood
would have been less tedious.

320
00:24:01,000 --> 00:24:04,720
One can
watch an electric counter, too.

321
00:24:04,880 --> 00:24:05,840
It moves, too.

322
00:24:06,000 --> 00:24:08,080
But it's silent,
it doesn't go clac-clac,

323
00:24:08,240 --> 00:24:10,160
so, it's less interesting.

324
00:24:10,560 --> 00:24:13,560
Yes, you must have done
strange things when you were little.

325
00:24:13,720 --> 00:24:15,720
I spent my time at the casino,
watching the roulette turn.

326
00:24:15,840 --> 00:24:18,080
watching the roulette turn.

327
00:24:18,240 --> 00:24:19,920
Yes, it's true.

328
00:24:20,080 --> 00:24:24,400
My parents were diplomats,
but baby-sitters were expensive,

329
00:24:24,560 --> 00:24:26,520
so they brought me to
the casino in the evening.

330
00:24:26,680 --> 00:24:28,720
And as I was
very good with martingale,

331
00:24:28,880 --> 00:24:30,760
I won the bank every night.

332
00:24:30,960 --> 00:24:33,520
So they banned me,
but I didn't care,

333
00:24:33,680 --> 00:24:34,960
because by that time,

334
00:24:35,120 --> 00:24:38,320
I was able to pay for
a babysitter myself.

335
00:24:39,080 --> 00:24:42,480
- You don't believe me.
- Oh, yes, I do.

336
00:24:42,680 --> 00:24:47,000
It's a known fact. In Las Vegas,
there's a casino named after you.

337
00:24:47,160 --> 00:24:49,080
See, you don't believe me.

338
00:25:03,400 --> 00:25:05,280
Did you put it on cotton?

339
00:25:16,040 --> 00:25:17,200
Yes.

340
00:25:20,880 --> 00:25:23,000
- What is it?
- It's for Mr Mortez.

341
00:25:23,160 --> 00:25:25,400
- There was a call from Paris.
- Pst!

342
00:25:25,600 --> 00:25:28,480
- He's sleeping.
- Oh! I'm sorry.

343
00:25:28,680 --> 00:25:31,960
There. Mr Mortez is to call
Mr Gaultier, at the radio.

344
00:25:32,120 --> 00:25:34,400
He said it was urgent.
He'll be there until eight PM.

345
00:25:34,520 --> 00:25:36,200
Very good, we will, thank you.

346
00:25:36,400 --> 00:25:39,760
- Excuse me.
- No worries, he was sleeping...

347
00:25:42,640 --> 00:25:44,120
What was it?

348
00:25:44,280 --> 00:25:46,800
Oh, nothing, somebody
came to the wrong room.

349
00:25:48,240 --> 00:25:52,240
- Pretty?
- No, not really.

350
00:25:52,720 --> 00:25:55,520
Oh, well, what a pity.

351
00:25:58,640 --> 00:26:01,680
Shame, shame. Shit!

352
00:26:02,240 --> 00:26:05,920
- What's on TV tonight?
- We don't have TV.

353
00:26:06,120 --> 00:26:09,600
- Well, congratulations to that!
- I'm going to sleep, I'm beat.

354
00:26:09,760 --> 00:26:12,440
At this time?
Let's go to town?

355
00:26:12,600 --> 00:26:14,440
Vésilly by night...

356
00:26:14,600 --> 00:26:18,200
Mademoiselle,
we'd like to hang out a bit.

357
00:26:18,360 --> 00:26:20,000
What do you suggest?

358
00:26:20,160 --> 00:26:23,200
Well, it's nine PM,
everything is closed.

359
00:26:23,360 --> 00:26:24,840
What's at the movies?

360
00:26:25,000 --> 00:26:27,200
I don't know,
I'll ask Madame.

361
00:26:27,360 --> 00:26:30,320
Madam Tarrère, do you know
what they're showing at the Caméo?

362
00:26:30,480 --> 00:26:34,480
It's... D r Shivago,
b ut the movie has already started.

363
00:26:35,400 --> 00:26:38,760
As I've mentioned,
we're not tired.

364
00:26:38,920 --> 00:26:42,120
How about a game,
like Scrabble, for instance?

365
00:26:42,280 --> 00:26:44,360
- Oh, not a Scrabble!
- A what?

366
00:26:44,520 --> 00:26:47,760
Scrabble is a game
in which you form words out of

367
00:26:47,920 --> 00:26:49,720
the available letters.

368
00:26:49,880 --> 00:26:52,720
I don't understand. Our clientele
consists mainly of agents.

369
00:26:52,880 --> 00:26:54,520
Tell me about it.

370
00:26:54,680 --> 00:26:57,560
If you like, I'll go get
my son's Monopoly.

371
00:26:57,680 --> 00:26:59,000
Oh, yes! That's great!

372
00:26:59,160 --> 00:27:01,280
You'll see,
Monopoly is hilarious.

373
00:27:01,440 --> 00:27:05,000
- Perfect, is the game interesting?
- No.

374
00:27:05,200 --> 00:27:09,080
So, we'll be bored as hell.

375
00:27:10,440 --> 00:27:14,680
There, I'll buy Rue de La Paix,
that'll hurt.

376
00:27:15,200 --> 00:27:18,120
I'm sure the casino is open?
Shall we go?

377
00:27:18,240 --> 00:27:20,440
No, why don't you go, Michel.

378
00:27:20,600 --> 00:27:23,760
If you have seven,
you'll get to me, it'll cost you.

379
00:27:23,920 --> 00:27:26,040
You'll owe me 60 000.

380
00:27:27,040 --> 00:27:29,120
Oh, no! The houses. Ah! I failed.

381
00:27:29,320 --> 00:27:31,560
I almost got you.

382
00:27:31,720 --> 00:27:34,160
- I'm done. You win.
- No!

383
00:27:34,360 --> 00:27:36,520
You can still come back.

384
00:27:36,680 --> 00:27:40,400
You can keep playing alone,
I'm going to sleep.

385
00:27:41,320 --> 00:27:44,040
Yes, playing Monopoly alone,
thanks very much.

386
00:27:44,200 --> 00:27:45,200
You're not funny.

387
00:27:45,360 --> 00:27:47,520
For once we were having fun.
There! Ha!

388
00:27:47,680 --> 00:27:49,520
We'll play dice to establish

389
00:27:49,680 --> 00:27:51,840
who takes the small
and who takes the big bed.

390
00:27:52,040 --> 00:27:54,880
Take the big one, I don't care.

391
00:27:57,360 --> 00:28:00,280
Who will clean up?
Yours truly.

392
00:28:00,920 --> 00:28:02,880
Who'll put you to bed?

393
00:28:04,680 --> 00:28:07,200
Hep, the dirty laundry.

394
00:28:08,960 --> 00:28:11,520
So, when do
your fucking parents get back?

395
00:28:14,040 --> 00:28:16,840
You don't know?
Nor do I.

396
00:28:17,000 --> 00:28:19,800
You can't stay here,
we're already two in the room.

397
00:28:21,400 --> 00:28:23,280
And the other isn't exactly a doll.

398
00:28:25,400 --> 00:28:27,520
Is someone here?

399
00:28:53,280 --> 00:28:54,840
Give me 500 Francs.

400
00:28:55,000 --> 00:28:57,080
- What time is it?
- Stop your moaning.

401
00:28:57,280 --> 00:28:59,000
Give me 500 Francs.

402
00:29:43,560 --> 00:29:45,880
What?
Another sighting of a red dog.

403
00:29:46,000 --> 00:29:46,840
No. Look.

404
00:29:47,480 --> 00:29:49,000
- What?
- The counter shows

405
00:29:49,200 --> 00:29:51,800
83 138 km.
- So?

406
00:29:51,960 --> 00:29:56,160
83 138, a number you can
read from left to right, and

407
00:29:56,360 --> 00:29:58,000
from right to left.

408
00:29:58,400 --> 00:30:00,960
- Yes, so?
- That's all.

409
00:30:01,120 --> 00:30:02,720
Isn't that great?

410
00:30:03,760 --> 00:30:06,400
I bet 500 Francs that
you don't know the next number

411
00:30:06,560 --> 00:30:07,880
that works in both directions.

412
00:30:09,720 --> 00:30:11,440
- No.
- No?

413
00:30:11,560 --> 00:30:14,240
83 238.

414
00:30:16,400 --> 00:30:19,680
- You owe me 500 Francs.
- No, I didn't bet.

415
00:30:33,560 --> 00:30:34,840
Are you crazy?

416
00:30:36,080 --> 00:30:39,320
I'm sorry, it's because...
I believed a bicycle...

417
00:30:39,520 --> 00:30:40,720
on the bridge.

418
00:31:25,560 --> 00:31:29,240
Of course I believe you, my love.
How would I not believe you?

419
00:31:29,400 --> 00:31:30,480
But...

420
00:31:30,640 --> 00:31:34,600
But ...
Oh, let me speak!

421
00:31:34,720 --> 00:31:36,840
Oh! That you... Yes!

422
00:31:37,000 --> 00:31:40,800
Wed... wednesday.
But you must warn them.

423
00:31:41,240 --> 00:31:43,200
No, don't tell me...

424
00:31:45,440 --> 00:31:47,720
Ah! How I love you!

425
00:31:51,400 --> 00:31:55,120
Of course. Of course, I'll tell him.

426
00:31:55,880 --> 00:31:58,520
I promise, I'll tell him.

427
00:31:59,280 --> 00:32:01,320
If you wish, yes.

428
00:32:01,800 --> 00:32:05,520
The blue one,
you'll wear the blue one, ok?

429
00:32:11,000 --> 00:32:13,960
A letter for Mortez? Michel.
We have a reservation for one room.

430
00:32:14,120 --> 00:32:17,280
- Mr. Mortez. Hold on, I'll check.
- Go, quick!

431
00:32:17,880 --> 00:32:19,840
Nothing on that name, I'm afraid.

432
00:32:20,000 --> 00:32:22,640
- What time does the mail come in?
- 10 o'clock, Sir.

433
00:32:22,800 --> 00:32:24,600
Very well, we'll be gone.

434
00:32:24,760 --> 00:32:27,600
Michel,
all is well, we have a room.

435
00:32:28,040 --> 00:32:30,360
- Michel Mortez...
- Sir.

436
00:32:30,520 --> 00:32:31,640
From the radio.

437
00:32:34,920 --> 00:32:37,440
- There, Sirs. Is that all?
- Yes, thank you.

438
00:32:42,600 --> 00:32:47,000
- What's happening, Michel?
- I'm having a panic attack.

439
00:32:47,160 --> 00:32:49,280
Lay down for five minutes,
it'll be over soon.

440
00:32:49,440 --> 00:32:51,280
Two beds,
the night table in the middle,

441
00:32:51,480 --> 00:32:53,840
with golden ornamentations,
the artwork,

442
00:32:54,000 --> 00:32:55,920
the tiny little bathroom,

443
00:32:56,320 --> 00:32:58,520
the shiny synthetique bedcover,

444
00:32:58,680 --> 00:33:00,960
the smell, the fucking smell!

445
00:33:01,120 --> 00:33:03,680
It's a hotel room.
I don't see the problem.

446
00:33:03,840 --> 00:33:06,960
Rivetot, get me out of here.
I can't breathe, I'll scream.

447
00:33:09,400 --> 00:33:10,800
Michel!

448
00:33:32,400 --> 00:33:34,960
Michel, can I ask you a question?

449
00:33:35,120 --> 00:33:36,440
Yes, go ahead.

450
00:33:37,960 --> 00:33:40,520
Is it true that you were
Martine Carol's lover?

451
00:33:42,000 --> 00:33:43,520
Who told you this?

452
00:33:43,720 --> 00:33:45,760
Friends, at the radio.

453
00:33:45,920 --> 00:33:47,560
They say it,
but nobody knows for sure.

454
00:33:49,880 --> 00:33:51,120
What do you think?

455
00:33:51,960 --> 00:33:53,200
I don't know.

456
00:33:54,000 --> 00:33:56,920
If they say it,
it must be true.

457
00:34:04,880 --> 00:34:07,760
Have you been
intimate with other actresses?

458
00:34:07,960 --> 00:34:09,560
Singers, Dancers?

459
00:34:09,720 --> 00:34:12,120
We weren't bored after the war.

460
00:34:12,800 --> 00:34:14,560
- We weren't bored.
- I mean...

461
00:34:14,800 --> 00:34:17,440
- Those who were famous?
- Also, yes.

462
00:34:19,560 --> 00:34:21,440
But you're too young.

463
00:34:31,840 --> 00:34:32,680
Do you dance?

464
00:34:33,240 --> 00:34:34,240
Huh?

465
00:34:34,440 --> 00:34:35,680
Don't you like dancing?

466
00:34:35,880 --> 00:34:38,000
I do,
but, I mean, please...

467
00:34:39,560 --> 00:34:41,160
- Fine. Should we go?
- Oh, no.

468
00:34:46,000 --> 00:34:47,640
You had too much to drink.

469
00:34:47,800 --> 00:34:49,680
Yes,
but it doesn't mean I can't dance.

470
00:34:49,840 --> 00:34:51,840
You can drive, if you like.

471
00:34:54,320 --> 00:34:57,920
No, thanks. Be kind.
Not tonight, I'm tired.

472
00:34:58,600 --> 00:35:00,280
You're not funny.

473
00:35:01,520 --> 00:35:04,960
We're always together,
yet we hardly know each other.

474
00:35:06,800 --> 00:35:10,720
It's a funny feeling.
A strange sensation.

475
00:35:13,120 --> 00:35:14,840
Yes, it's bizarre.

476
00:35:28,400 --> 00:35:31,120
We don't know each other,
but we do like each other well.

477
00:35:33,280 --> 00:35:35,880
Sure, Michel. Sure.

478
00:35:39,480 --> 00:35:41,160
So, all is well.

479
00:36:29,000 --> 00:36:31,720
Come, on, Michel.
It's three o'clock, I'm dead tired.

480
00:36:31,880 --> 00:36:36,120
Quarter to. Do you think
that I can't read a watch?

481
00:36:36,280 --> 00:36:38,880
Close the door a bit,
It's always open.

482
00:36:41,520 --> 00:36:45,160
If you don't go out,
you'll get back by yourself.

483
00:36:45,320 --> 00:36:46,960
Get out! Get out already!

484
00:36:48,120 --> 00:36:51,440
Mortez isn't
completely knackered yet.

485
00:36:53,640 --> 00:36:57,440
Have you combed through him yet?
Well, no, no.

486
00:36:57,880 --> 00:37:00,120
He's still standing.

487
00:37:02,640 --> 00:37:04,320
You're still here?

488
00:37:07,560 --> 00:37:10,040
You're bonkers.
You've already lost enough tonight.

489
00:37:10,160 --> 00:37:12,160
You don't know what you're doing.

490
00:37:12,320 --> 00:37:16,840
Hep! 50 000 Francs, 50 mil.
Piss off!

491
00:37:17,000 --> 00:37:19,760
You're so dissapointing,
when you're drunk.

492
00:37:20,720 --> 00:37:22,600
You're not throwing away
50 grand, are you?

493
00:37:22,800 --> 00:37:24,840
What does it look like,
you little shit?

494
00:37:25,040 --> 00:37:28,320
I'm a lord.
Lord Mortez.

495
00:37:28,440 --> 00:37:32,040
And Lord Mortez decided
to have fun tonight?

496
00:37:32,200 --> 00:37:34,040
Chips!

497
00:37:34,200 --> 00:37:36,400
