00:55:55,280 --> 00:55:57,640
Do you know
what they invented in Sweden?

749
00:55:58,640 --> 00:56:02,440
They managed to
create a kind of white grass,

750
00:56:02,600 --> 00:56:04,000
like chicory.

751
00:56:05,280 --> 00:56:09,800
A plant without photosynthesis,
not green, but white.

752
00:56:11,560 --> 00:56:14,360
They grew it on the side
and then in the middle of the road.

753
00:56:15,080 --> 00:56:17,880
This way they don't need to
paint white stripes on the street.

754
00:56:18,040 --> 00:56:19,800
Clever, isn't it?

755
00:56:20,520 --> 00:56:21,800
Brilliant.

756
00:56:23,040 --> 00:56:26,160
Poor fellow, you'd believe anything.

757
00:56:34,080 --> 00:56:34,880
Are you sleeping?

758
00:56:35,080 --> 00:56:38,560
What? No.
Just a little slump.

759
00:56:40,040 --> 00:56:41,040
Should I drive?

760
00:56:41,280 --> 00:56:44,520
- Pardon?
- Should I drive?

761
00:56:45,120 --> 00:56:48,200
Oh, yes, please,
I didn't want to bother you...

762
00:56:55,120 --> 00:56:57,920
Do you have a permit?
What if the police catches us...

763
00:56:59,520 --> 00:57:00,720
Oh, no!

764
00:57:02,000 --> 00:57:03,200
I believe you.

765
00:57:03,400 --> 00:57:06,440
I only said that to avoid trouble.

766
00:57:13,040 --> 00:57:15,600
- You look young on that picture.
- Thank you.

767
00:57:15,760 --> 00:57:16,680
How old?

768
00:57:17,120 --> 00:57:20,080
- 20.
- That explains it.

769
00:57:20,240 --> 00:57:22,480
When you'll be 50
you'll still look the same,

770
00:57:22,680 --> 00:57:25,960
rightfully so,
you look like 50 now.

771
00:57:26,760 --> 00:57:29,800
Shall we continue being mean
or should we stop?

772
00:57:31,560 --> 00:57:34,360
Michel Morteau. Mort...

773
00:57:34,520 --> 00:57:36,360
- Mortez, isn't your real name?
- No,

774
00:57:36,560 --> 00:57:38,200
it's a pseudonyme.

775
00:57:38,720 --> 00:57:41,040
In those days,
South America was fashionable,

776
00:57:41,200 --> 00:57:44,440
so I changed it from
Morteau to Mortez

777
00:57:45,040 --> 00:57:48,520
to sound more exotic.

778
00:57:48,680 --> 00:57:51,880
To sound exotic, you could have
changed your christian name.

779
00:57:52,040 --> 00:57:54,880
Miguel. Miguel Mortez,
sound good.

780
00:57:55,080 --> 00:57:57,600
You'd have been complimented
to speak spanish without an accent.

781
00:57:57,760 --> 00:58:01,360
With that name,
you'd have been an operetta singer.

782
00:58:01,520 --> 00:58:03,560
Like Luis Mariano.

783
00:58:03,760 --> 00:58:06,360
I didn't think of that.
Life is terrible.

784
00:58:06,520 --> 00:58:08,720
I should have met you sooner.

785
00:58:10,120 --> 00:58:12,080
Are..are you in a bad mood?

786
00:59:18,040 --> 00:59:21,600
- What? What's happening?
- Nothing. Sleep.

787
00:59:39,720 --> 00:59:41,720
Enough. You've eaten enough!

788
00:59:41,880 --> 00:59:44,440
There's a limit, you know?
Up, up! Pack up.

789
00:59:45,080 --> 00:59:47,960
You're an embarrassment
to our country.

790
00:59:48,160 --> 00:59:52,320
I love winter, just because
you're not out and about.

791
00:59:52,480 --> 00:59:55,160
There should be
a fashion brigade forbidding

792
00:59:55,360 --> 00:59:58,520
tracksuits outside
of soccer stadiums.

793
00:59:59,040 --> 01:00:01,840
- You're hurting yourself, Michel.
- They're multiplying.

794
01:00:02,000 --> 01:00:05,320
They should be deprived
of custody over there children,

795
01:00:05,440 --> 01:00:07,160
no: we'll sterilize them!

796
01:00:07,360 --> 01:00:10,400
Yes, come one.
We'll be late for the show.

797
01:00:11,360 --> 01:00:13,040
You think that this
is my audience?

798
01:00:13,240 --> 01:00:15,760
No, there's all those
having lunch at home.

799
01:00:16,960 --> 01:00:17,960
Frenchmen!

800
01:00:20,080 --> 01:00:21,920
You're crazy, Michel!

801
01:00:24,600 --> 01:00:28,160
- Go on, start the car!
- Bloody car!

802
01:00:28,360 --> 01:00:30,000
So?

803
01:00:30,160 --> 01:00:33,200
She always does that,
when she's hot.

804
01:00:33,400 --> 01:00:35,000
Holy shit!

805
01:00:36,400 --> 01:00:39,880
- We're fucked, she's drowned.
- What do we do now?

806
01:00:40,080 --> 01:00:42,160
What do you want to do?
We've broken down.

807
01:00:42,320 --> 01:00:44,840
We'll hitchhike.
With all the equipment.

808
01:00:45,000 --> 01:00:47,280
The show is in 45 minutes.
We're fucked.

809
01:00:48,160 --> 01:00:49,400
Listen, Rivetot.

810
01:00:50,320 --> 01:00:53,120
In 25 years,
I've never missed one show.

811
01:00:53,320 --> 01:00:56,320
Sick, high fever...
never, have I let down

812
01:00:56,520 --> 01:00:57,920
my audience.

813
01:00:58,080 --> 01:01:00,200
I'm not going to let
a car run my life.

814
01:01:01,120 --> 01:01:02,800
I'm sorry, Michel.

815
01:01:05,080 --> 01:01:06,520
Don't move.

816
01:01:09,960 --> 01:01:13,520
I'm sorry about earlier.
I don't know what came over me.

817
01:01:13,720 --> 01:01:17,640
There, I'm Miguel Mort...
Michel Mortez, from the radio.

818
01:01:17,800 --> 01:01:19,280
You know? The Cat's Tongue.

819
01:01:19,440 --> 01:01:21,760
Our show is in 40 minutes.

820
01:01:21,920 --> 01:01:24,520
We've a problem with our car.

821
01:01:24,680 --> 01:01:25,840
So, I wonder

822
01:01:26,000 --> 01:01:28,960
if you could help us out.

823
01:01:39,880 --> 01:01:42,040
It's 12.45,
time for our live show

824
01:01:42,240 --> 01:01:44,040
with Michel Mortez
and the Cat's Tongue.

825
01:01:44,200 --> 01:01:46,560
Today you're in Brécances?

826
01:01:46,760 --> 01:01:51,280
We're not in Brecances,
but about 20 km away.

827
01:01:51,480 --> 01:01:54,200
In fact,
we're doing an experiment today

828
01:01:54,360 --> 01:01:56,880
which will
enter into the annals of radio:

829
01:01:57,040 --> 01:02:00,720
a completely improvised show,
in presence of

830
01:02:00,880 --> 01:02:02,200
these charming vacationers,

831
01:02:02,360 --> 01:02:06,160
who were quietly having lunch
on the side of the street.

832
01:02:06,480 --> 01:02:09,240
Our first question is for Mr Gora,

833
01:02:09,440 --> 01:02:14,240
our first candidate:
"German doctor and microbiologist

834
01:02:14,440 --> 01:02:17,720
"born in Clausthal in 1843,
died in 1910,

835
01:02:17,920 --> 01:02:20,440
"this great scientist
saved millions of human lives,

836
01:02:20,640 --> 01:02:23,360
"discovering, in 1882,

837
01:02:24,040 --> 01:02:26,120
"the bacteria of tuberculosis."

838
01:02:26,280 --> 01:02:28,560
You have 30 seconds to answer.

839
01:02:28,760 --> 01:02:31,960
- Top stop!
- Is he very famous?

840
01:02:32,160 --> 01:02:36,160
Yes, very well-known.
The bacillus is named after him.

841
01:02:36,320 --> 01:02:39,440
Could you stop eating
during the questions?

842
01:02:41,480 --> 01:02:43,800
I don't know. Einstein?

843
01:02:45,280 --> 01:02:48,080
No, it's not Einstein.
It was..

844
01:02:48,280 --> 01:02:49,080
Robert Koch.

845
01:02:49,240 --> 01:02:52,560
You never heard of
the Koch Bacillus?

846
01:02:54,000 --> 01:02:57,560
I don't think so.
No, I haven't, sorry.

847
01:02:57,760 --> 01:03:01,400
That's ok, Mr. Gora.
Here's an easier question.

848
01:03:01,600 --> 01:03:04,520
"Which monumental statue
was built by Batholdi?"

849
01:03:04,720 --> 01:03:07,280
Top stop!
I can give you a hint,

850
01:03:07,440 --> 01:03:10,240
the statue stands in
the harbour of New York.

851
01:03:10,400 --> 01:03:12,240
Hm, I don't know. No.

852
01:03:12,600 --> 01:03:14,360
We're getting
to the end of our show.

853
01:03:14,520 --> 01:03:16,480
Our candidates
weren't too lucky today,

854
01:03:16,640 --> 01:03:19,920
alas, not answering,
any of our questions.

855
01:03:20,080 --> 01:03:22,680
Here's back to our studios.

856
01:03:22,840 --> 01:03:24,680
back to Paris!

857
01:03:25,240 --> 01:03:27,600
Thank you. Really.
You saved our show.

858
01:03:27,720 --> 01:03:29,080
Welcome.

859
01:03:30,080 --> 01:03:32,760
Wait.
You're not leaving now, are you?

860
01:03:33,120 --> 01:03:34,920
You're having desert with us.

861
01:03:35,080 --> 01:03:36,760
With pleasure.

862
01:03:40,520 --> 01:03:44,560
You're show is great.
My wife and I listen to it.

863
01:03:44,840 --> 01:03:48,120
Even in sport questions,
I never know the answer.

864
01:03:59,000 --> 01:04:01,640
Sir!
There's a message for Mr. Mortez.

865
01:04:01,800 --> 01:04:04,840
He has to call Mr. Gaultier
before five PM this evening.

866
01:04:05,000 --> 01:04:08,240
- Here's the number.
- Oh, I know his number.

867
01:04:08,400 --> 01:04:10,160
He doesn't seem too jolly.

868
01:04:11,600 --> 01:04:13,520
Yes, Rivetot, here, Mr. Gaultier.

869
01:04:14,840 --> 01:04:19,400
He's not here,
but he asked me to call you.

870
01:04:21,800 --> 01:04:22,960
What?

871
01:04:23,560 --> 01:04:25,000
No, but...

872
01:04:25,400 --> 01:04:28,160
You can't
cancel the show so abruptly.

873
01:04:28,320 --> 01:04:31,160
You'll kill him.
Leave him a few days, at least.

874
01:04:33,320 --> 01:04:35,680
No, we never received your letters.

875
01:04:36,640 --> 01:04:38,520
No messages, nothing.

876
01:04:39,320 --> 01:04:42,440
Why would we have called?
We didn't know.

877
01:04:44,720 --> 01:04:46,040
Well.

878
01:04:46,880 --> 01:04:50,480
I'll speak to him when he returns.
He'll call you.

879
01:04:54,040 --> 01:04:55,280
Alright.

880
01:04:56,840 --> 01:05:01,080
Yes, just one thing,
you're a bastard.

881
01:05:01,960 --> 01:05:03,720
Goodbye, Mr. Gaultier.

882
01:05:06,840 --> 01:05:09,520
You know, today's show
really cheered me up.

883
01:05:09,680 --> 01:05:11,000
I didn't realize it,

884
01:05:11,160 --> 01:05:15,400
but the idea
of improvising is pure genius.

885
01:05:15,560 --> 01:05:18,240
Not like the purr of
a prepared candidate.

886
01:05:18,400 --> 01:05:21,800
- Don't you find? No?
- Yes, sure.

887
01:05:23,840 --> 01:05:26,840
- You don't seem enthusiastic.
- Yes, I loved it.

888
01:05:27,640 --> 01:05:30,040
- You don't mind my coat?
- Ah! Sorry.

889
01:05:32,720 --> 01:05:35,440
I'm seeing Gaultier friday.
I have some suggestions.

890
01:05:35,640 --> 01:05:37,520
The best would be
to do this on TV.

891
01:05:37,680 --> 01:05:40,560
Imagine: Surprise candidates,
live, on TV?

892
01:05:40,720 --> 01:05:42,720
It's good that
surprise candidate idea.

893
01:05:42,880 --> 01:05:46,080
I'd call it,..
The Surprise Candidate.

894
01:05:48,160 --> 01:05:51,120
Oh! I know someone who'll
be surprised in Paris on friday.

895
01:05:53,000 --> 01:05:54,240
Me, too.

896
01:06:38,080 --> 01:06:40,320
"Mexican politician,
born in 1880,

897
01:06:40,520 --> 01:06:43,920
"He rose up the peones
tr ying to make an agrarian reform,

898
01:06:44,040 --> 01:06:45,920
"but was killed in 1919.

899
01:06:46,080 --> 01:06:48,920
"Marlon Brando incarnated him
in the movie about his life."

900
01:06:50,000 --> 01:06:53,800
- Do you know who it is?
- No, I don't know? Who?

901
01:06:53,960 --> 01:06:55,040
You're not even looking.

902
01:06:55,240 --> 01:06:59,160
I am, but I don't know.
I'm not going to think for hours.

903
01:06:59,360 --> 01:07:01,360
As a hint,
I'll give you his initials:

904
01:07:01,560 --> 01:07:05,360
- E, Z.
- "E, Z"? That's not helping!

905
01:07:07,440 --> 01:07:08,520
Etienne Zaza?

906
01:07:08,720 --> 01:07:10,160
Eugène Zanzibar?

907
01:07:10,360 --> 01:07:13,480
- She's dead, get rid of it?
- It was about

908
01:07:13,680 --> 01:07:16,080
Emiliano Zapata.
It's really easy.

909
01:07:16,240 --> 01:07:19,080
No, keep that one.
I like it a lot.

910
01:07:24,760 --> 01:07:28,280
Go! When I raise my arm,
you cheer as much as you can.

911
01:07:28,440 --> 01:07:31,280
Attention! 1, 2, 3!

912
01:07:36,240 --> 01:07:38,800
That's a bit soft.
Lateron, you're going to...

913
01:07:40,800 --> 01:07:43,360
- Do you think it will be ok?
- I don't know, we'll see.

914
01:07:43,480 --> 01:07:45,160
It's going to have to.

915
01:07:45,720 --> 01:07:48,040
Hello, hello, hello.

916
01:07:48,200 --> 01:07:51,120
Attention! 1, 2, 3!

917
01:07:56,400 --> 01:07:58,480
Something's wrong,
there aren't many people,

918
01:07:58,640 --> 01:08:01,680
but I believe quality
replaced quantity.

919
01:08:02,560 --> 01:08:06,160
It's because of Bias Bicycle.
There all down there.

920
01:08:06,320 --> 01:08:07,720
No big deal.

921
01:08:07,880 --> 01:08:10,440
They seem nice,
I'm happy to be here.

922
01:08:10,600 --> 01:08:13,640
It reminds me of my beginnings.
Hello, my friends.

923
01:08:13,840 --> 01:08:15,440
Happy to be here?

924
01:08:18,160 --> 01:08:20,160
On the air in two minutes,
Michel.

925
01:08:22,840 --> 01:08:25,640
So, we got out
all our little equipment?

926
01:08:26,560 --> 01:08:27,840
I suppose so.

927
01:08:28,440 --> 01:08:30,880
What's your plan, Rivetot?
What the hell are you doing?

928
01:08:32,040 --> 01:08:34,440
What do you mean?

929
01:08:35,000 --> 01:08:36,120
Why are you doing all this?

930
01:08:36,880 --> 01:08:39,560
To avoid telling me that
the show's been cancelled?

931
01:08:39,720 --> 01:08:41,840
What are you doing tomorrow
and the day after?

932
01:08:42,000 --> 01:08:44,320
Another fake show
with fake candidates,

933
01:08:44,480 --> 01:08:45,840
and a fake pensionary audience

934
01:08:46,040 --> 01:08:47,960
that you picked up
at the local elderly home?

935
01:08:50,000 --> 01:08:52,120
- Let me explain...
- Never mind.

936
01:08:54,400 --> 01:08:55,880
I know everything.

937
01:08:59,600 --> 01:09:02,200
How long have you known?

938
01:09:07,440 --> 01:09:08,880
Shit!

939
01:09:10,320 --> 01:09:13,160
Don't worry.
It wasn't in vain.

940
01:09:14,600 --> 01:09:16,680
We'll do your show.

941
01:09:19,320 --> 01:09:20,120
Erbussonais,

942
01:09:20,320 --> 01:09:23,160
Erbussonaises,
how are you feeling?

943
01:09:28,320 --> 01:09:30,680
Hidden in the folds
of the Perche hills,

944
01:09:30,840 --> 01:09:32,960
Erbusson is a mideval town

945
01:09:33,160 --> 01:09:35,200
with a very rich past,

946
01:09:35,360 --> 01:09:37,720
celebrated
for its food specialties...

947
01:09:55,560 --> 01:09:59,480
Yes, yes, hello.
Hello, it's me.

948
01:10:00,280 --> 01:10:03,240
Oh, my love, I'm so happy
to hear your voice.

949
01:10:03,880 --> 01:10:06,800
A day without you is a lost day.

950
01:10:07,560 --> 01:10:08,720
Well, I'm coming back tonight.

951
01:10:09,240 --> 01:10:13,320
No, no nothing's wrong.
I'll explain later.

952
01:10:13,960 --> 01:10:17,280
So, I'll be there
before you leave for Buenos Aires.

953
01:10:17,480 --> 01:10:21,600
No! I'll explain.

954
01:10:22,880 --> 01:10:24,840
I love you, sweetheart.

955
01:10:25,440 --> 01:10:30,040
I realize
that I miss you more each day.

956
01:10:31,720 --> 01:10:33,440
Oh, no. Shit!

957
01:10:39,920 --> 01:10:41,680
Michel! Hello, madam?

958
01:10:41,880 --> 01:10:46,040
- He's ...
- At the fourth top it will be...

959
01:10:46,920 --> 01:10:50,320
13.44.

960
01:10:56,600 --> 01:11:01,040
13.44 and ten seconds,

961
01:11:04,080 --> 01:11:08,760
13 h 44 and twenty seconds,

962
01:11:08,920 --> 01:11:10,320
Are you ok?

963
01:11:11,760 --> 01:11:13,160
Sure.

964
01:11:28,040 --> 01:11:30,760
So? Did you see Gaultier?

965
01:11:32,680 --> 01:11:36,200
Let's have a drink?
It's on me.

966
01:11:40,520 --> 01:11:42,840
The adventurers are back.

967
01:11:43,240 --> 01:11:45,560
So, Mr. Mortez,
still at ease?

968
01:11:47,360 --> 01:11:50,360
- What are you having?
- I don't care.

969
01:11:50,560 --> 01:11:52,680
Two small cognacs,
please, Gilles.

970
01:11:56,720 --> 01:12:00,440
I wanted to tell you...
I find it revolting!

971
01:12:08,920 --> 01:12:10,920
What's the matter now?

972
01:12:11,120 --> 01:12:13,760
We keep going until christmas,
but only every other day.

973
01:12:14,120 --> 01:12:17,200
Pick me up tomorrow morning,
at six o clock at my house. Bye.

974
01:12:17,400 --> 01:12:19,000
Where are you heading?
Should I drop you?

975
01:12:19,160 --> 01:12:20,720
I got the new CX.

976
01:12:20,880 --> 01:12:24,200
You know, the new, the Citroën!

977
01:12:26,360 --> 01:12:28,880
How does this rubbish stop?

978
01:12:30,200 --> 01:12:31,560
Ah, finally.

979
01:12:52,520 --> 01:12:53,720
Michel?

980
01:13:07,080 --> 01:13:08,360
Are you there?

981
01:13:22,320 --> 01:13:25,720
Michel? It's Rivetot.

982
01:14:37,600 --> 01:14:40,760
- Let's go, Rivetot?
- Michel!

983
01:14:46,680 --> 01:14:48,080
Are you well?

984
01:14:49,760 --> 01:14:51,440
Let's go, Rivetot?

985
01:14:58,000 --> 01:15:02,280
Bus seats, power steering,
hydropneumatic suspensions...

986
01:15:02,560 --> 01:15:03,880
With this car, I don't mind

987
01:15:04,080 --> 01:15:05,920
traveling across France.

988
01:15:10,680 --> 01:15:12,040
I love new cars.

989
01:15:13,280 --> 01:15:14,720
It smells new.

990
01:15:17,120 --> 01:15:19,360
See this? Electric windows!

991
01:15:19,600 --> 01:15:22,080
Some fresh air?
Ask me.

992
01:15:23,560 --> 01:15:27,520
It's like a new toy for a child.
Great, isn't it?

993
01:15:29,200 --> 01:15:32,160
Well, I'll close it,
or you'll catch cold.

994
01:15:35,360 --> 01:15:37,320
Lower the window,
you trapped my hair.

995
01:15:38,800 --> 01:15:39,960
Sorry.

996
01:15:42,480 --> 01:15:43,480
Attention!

